    <ThingDef Name="PPK_GA" ParentName="BaseMakeableGun_GA">
        <defName>Gun_PPK_GA</defName>
        <label>Walther PPK</label>
        <description>The PP and the PPK were among the world's first successful double action semi-automatic pistols. They are still manufactured by Walther and have been widely copied. The design inspired other pistols, among them the Soviet Makarov and the American Accu-Tek AT-380 II. The PP and PPK were both popular with European police and civilians for being reliable and concealable. During World War II, they were issued to the German military, including the Luftwaffe, as well as the police.</description>
